natural problem: A printer prints 17 pages per minute. How many minutes will it take to print 200 pages? Express your answer to the nearest whole number.

a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes pages_per_minute pages :: real
assumes h0 : "pages_per_minute = 17"
shows  "(pages / pages_per_minute) = 12"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 A printer prints 17 pages per minute. How many minutes will it take to print 200 pages? Express your answer to the nearest whole number. The final Answer is 12
 ### Proof
 $\frac{200 \text{ pages}}{17 \text{ pages per minute}} \approx \boxed{12}$ minutes.
 *)

theorem
fixes pages_per_minute pages :: real
assumes h0 : "pages_per_minute = 17"
shows  "(pages / pages_per_minute) = 12"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: If a person can read 17 pages per minute, how many pages can they read in 12 minutes?
